subSubSection.paragraph:
Saussurea talungensis

is currently recorded only from the type locality in Talung valley (between Nyalu Pass and Ning Tsho), Humla district, NW Nepal (Fig. 
1A-D
). It grows on the alpine open gravelly or stony slopes at an elevation ca. 4300 m a.s.l. (Fig. 
1C, D
).
